## Implementación via Observers

```php
// app/Domain/Workspaces/Observers/WorkspaceObserver.php

class WorkspaceObserver
{
    public function created(Workspace $workspace): void
    {
        ActivityLogger::log(
            action:      'workspace.created',
            subject:     $workspace,
            workspaceId: $workspace->id,
            after:       $workspace->toLogArray(),
        );
    }

    public function updated(Workspace $workspace): void
    {
        ActivityLogger::log(
            action:      'workspace.updated',
            subject:     $workspace,
            workspaceId: $workspace->id,
            before:      $workspace->getOriginal(),
            after:       $workspace->getDirty(),
        );
    }

    public function deleted(Workspace $workspace): void
    {
        ActivityLogger::log(
            action:      'workspace.deleted',
            subject:     $workspace,
            workspaceId: $workspace->id,
            before:      $workspace->toLogArray(),
        );
    }
}
```

---

## ActivityLogger helper

```php
// app/Domain/ActivityLogs/Services/ActivityLogger.php

class ActivityLogger
{
    public static function log(
        string $action,
        Model  $subject,
        ?int   $workspaceId  = null,
        ?int   $enterpriseId = null,
        ?int   $roomId       = null,
        mixed  $before       = null,
        mixed  $after        = null,
        mixed  $context      = null,
        ?string $reason      = null,
    ): void {
        ActivityLog::create([
            'actor_user_id'  => Auth::id(),
            'action'         => $action,
            'subject_type'   => class_basename($subject),
            'subject_id'     => $subject->getKey(),
            'workspace_id'   => $workspaceId,
            'enterprise_id'  => $enterpriseId,
            'room_id'        => $roomId,
            'metadata_json'  => compact('before', 'after', 'context', 'reason'),
            'ip_address'     => request()->ip(),
            'user_agent'     => request()->userAgent(),
        ]);
    }
}
```

Se puede registrar de forma asíncrona con `dispatch()` si el volumen es alto.

